President Muhammadu Buhari on Tuesday celebrated the General Overseer of Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG), Pastor Enoch Adeboye on the occasion of his birthday. Joining a host of others and RCCG members, President Buhari in his congratulatory message commended Pastor Adeboye for walking the path of a righteous man by dedicating his life to the service of God, and humanity. Celebrating the clergyman in a message issued by his Special Adviser on Media, Femi Adesina, Buhari appreciated Adeboye’s warmth and friendliness, which he also extended to leaders and others from all walks of life. Rising Crude Oil Prices, Opportunity For Nigeria — Buhari OPEC Lauds Buhari On Support For Energy Industry The president also felicitated his wife, Pastor Foluke Adeboye, family members, friends and relations as the General Overseer turns an octogenarian. He recalled his private and public meetings with the renowned preacher and teacher of the Bible over many years, most remarkably the visit when he was recuperating in London in 2017. According to the president, Adeboye’s contributions to the betterment of Nigeria and other countries stand out clearly as testimonies of his divine calling. He also lauded him for impacting greatly on the nation’s education, health and infrastructural development, which include many urban and rural roads. The president saluted the focus of the RCCG leader on works of the Kingdom and peace for the nation, praying that his path would be like a shining light, with grace for good health and strength.